title: Bug 121170: Inconsistent results when calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before/after data extraction
description: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before/after data extraction, the returned labels are different.
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before extracting data, it returns incorrect or incomplete labels that are not recognizable to the user.
EB: The method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable labels both before and after data extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Call the IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method before extracting any data.
2. Call the IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method after data extraction.
3. Compare the returned labels before and after extraction. You should observe that they are different.
